enaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 2971<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/22/03 2:58:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=162.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2001/05/images/021011_nuclear.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/Bart-term.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Spring Launcher</span><hr size=1> How much weight to pull down a spring like that? A hell of a lot. I've lost my calculator. There will have to be a very big hole under the spring and strong platform to support the spring base I guess. <br>
